Hi Matthias, Max, Martin

I've just had a good call with the team to pull together the below activiti=
es and tasks in order to push forward with New Dispo and the tight timeline=
 we have in front of us.

I've spilt out the activities I'm aware of/ need completing:

P3 Activities:

  *
Provide developer list of who needs access to ENT1 Oracle (dev environment)=
 - hopefully all who have cal-consult.de address to date.
  *
Provide list of users who need access to the ABN1060 database
  *
Provide a list of users who need access to the ABN1060 - TMS Application
  *
Creation of Technical document outlining (inclusive design for both Oracle =
and Postgres)
     *
Database user accounts required

     *
Database user permissions required

     *
Decision and design for CDC selection

     *
Required APIs running in GCP
     *
GCP services running
     *
GCP service accounts running
     *
Other GCP configuration that we aren't aware of.
  *
Creation in GCP wl4-t-: (in line with Technical design document)

     *
NEW UAT- NEW Dispo

     *
NEW DEV- NEW Dispo (do this last in case we can solve the WL4 Dev challenge=
)

  *
Creation in GCP WL5-d: (in line with Technical design document)
     *
NEW DEV - TMS Bridge (ready to be deployed into)

NB: We have an issue at the moment for the creation of WL4-dev - Ron and I =
are working through this but the instructions we've got from the legacy Con=
straight team aren't complete nor clear enough for us to create the WL4 at =
the moment. To get round this please create the required in WL4-t- this won=
't cause any issues.

Nagel Activities:

  *
Copy for 1060 - into ABN1060 - Platform (excluded from 7.0.0.8 - large Orac=
le change for now)
  *
Application setup of ABN1060 - Platform
  *
Oracle user creation (dependant on Technical design document) =3D
  *
TMS Oracle - DEVOPS setup to build out a Feature branch for NEW DISPO (Matt=
 with Alex F)
  *
Continuation of trying to create WL4 -d-

When we are ready we can turn on order duplication when required per enviro=
nment.

UAT environment:

  *
UAT1060 - access via Citrix - will be where Max and Patrick complete their =
testing.

Release schedule will be targeted every 2 weeks - to be confirmed when to s=
tart for Oracle.

Kind regards / Mit freundlichen Gr=FC=DFen / Met vriendelijke groet

